  SECTION 6 — CRASH RECOVERY  (Job: 18ba35fd-9f66-4fc4-a319-0fcba762bc15)
  Proves: a job killed mid-retry is never lost
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  STEP 1: Enqueue job
    POST /events  idempotency_key=crash-test-001  payload={"txn":"TXN-SURVIVE-KILL"}
    → HTTP 202  {"job_id":"18ba35fd-9f66-4fc4-a319-0fcba762bc15","status":"pending"}

  STEP 2: Workers make first 3 attempts (all fail with HTTP 500)
    dispatcher-1 | {"asctime":"2026-04-08T10:39:51Z","message":"[18ba35fd] Attempt 1 FAILED in 0.00s — retry in 1.8s at 10:39:53 UTC. Error: HTTP 500: {\"forced_fail\":\"1/5\"}"}
    dispatcher-1 | {"asctime":"2026-04-08T10:39:53Z","message":"[18ba35fd] Attempt 2 FAILED in 0.00s — retry in 3.6s at 10:39:57 UTC. Error: HTTP 500: {\"forced_fail\":\"2/5\"}"}
    dispatcher-1 | {"asctime":"2026-04-08T10:39:57Z","message":"[18ba35fd] Attempt 3 FAILED in 0.00s — retry in 8.0s at 10:40:05 UTC. Error: HTTP 500: {\"forced_fail\":\"3/5\"}"}
                                                                                              ↑ DISPATCHER KILLED HERE

  STEP 3: Kill dispatcher
    docker compose kill dispatcher
    → Container webhook-dispatcher-dispatcher-1 Killed

  STEP 4: Direct PostgreSQL query — job still safe
    SELECT id, status, attempt_count, next_attempt_at
    FROM webhook_jobs WHERE id='18ba35fd-...';

    ┌──────────────────────────────────────┬─────────┬───────────────┬────────────────────────────────┐
    │ id                                   │ status  │ attempt_count │ next_attempt_at                │
    ├──────────────────────────────────────┼─────────┼───────────────┼────────────────────────────────┤
    │ 18ba35fd-9f66-4fc4-a319-0fcba762bc15 │ pending │             3 │ 2026-04-08 10:40:05.523096+00  │
    └──────────────────────────────────────┴─────────┴───────────────┴────────────────────────────────┘
    JOB IS SAFE IN POSTGRESQL — not lost despite process kill.

  STEP 5: Restart dispatcher
    docker compose start dispatcher
    → Container webhook-dispatcher-dispatcher-1 Started

  STEP 6: Startup recovery log
    dispatcher-1 | {"asctime":"2026-04-08T10:40:12Z","name":"main",    "message":"=== Webhook Dispatcher starting up ==="}
    dispatcher-1 | {"asctime":"2026-04-08T10:40:13Z","name":"database","message":"Startup recovery: no stuck jobs found."}
