  SECTION 7 — MANUAL RETRY ENDPOINT  (Job: 51938fbf-daeb-4814-8fc8-fd5d569d70b2)
  POST /jobs/{id}/retry — re-enqueues a permanently failed job
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  STEP 1: Enqueue job with max_attempts=1 (forces permanent failure on first attempt)
    POST /events  event_type=refund.processed  idempotency_key=retry-test-001
    → job 51938fbf created

    dispatcher-1 | {"message":"[51938fbf] Attempt 1 FAILED in 0.00s — ..."}
    dispatcher-1 | {"levelname":"ERROR","message":"[51938fbf] PERMANENTLY FAILED after 2 attempts."}

  STEP 2: Confirm failed state
    GET /jobs/51938fbf-...
    → {"status":"failed","attempt_count":2,"max_attempts":1,
       "last_error":"HTTP 500: {\"error\":\"Simulated server error\",\"forced_fail\":\"2/5\"}"}

  STEP 3: Reset via retry endpoint
    POST /jobs/51938fbf-daeb-4814-8fc8-fd5d569d70b2/retry
    → HTTP 202  {"job_id":"51938fbf-...","status":"pending",
                 "message":"Job reset to pending. Delivery will be attempted shortly."}

  STEP 4: Confirm reset
    GET /jobs/51938fbf-...
    → {"status":"pending","attempt_count":0,"max_attempts":10,"last_error":null}

  STEP 5: Workers pick it up; delivered on attempt 4 (mock counter was at 2 from pre-retry)
    dispatcher-1 | {"message":"[51938fbf] DELIVERED on attempt 4 (0.00s)"}

    GET /jobs/51938fbf-...
    → {"status":"delivered","attempt_count":4}

  STEP 6: Guard — retry a delivered job → HTTP 409
    POST /jobs/48ffb20e-.../retry  (status=delivered)
    → HTTP 409  {"detail":"Job '48ffb20e-...' is in status='delivered'. Only 'failed' jobs can be retried."}

  RESULT: PASS — failed jobs reset to pending with fresh retry budget; non-failed jobs rejected


